Life Calendar Specification (v0.2)

1. Overview
- App name: Life Calendar
- Goal: visualize life in weeks so remaining time and current position are easy to grasp at a glance
- Concept:
  - prioritize visual clarity over dense information
  - favor calm awareness over pressure
  - keep the app light enough to revisit every day

2. Target Platforms
- iOS / Android with Expo / React Native
- Initial release uses local-only persistence

3. Current Functional Requirements
3.1 Onboarding
- Birth date input
- Life expectancy input
- Total-week preview
- Local persistence after onboarding completion

3.2 Main Screen
- Settings button in the top-right corner
- View mode switch at the top
  - `Life`: show the entire lifespan as a 52-column by N-year weekly grid
  - `Year`: show one year broken into month rows
- Remaining weeks and a progress meter at the bottom

3.3 Life Mode
- 1 cell = 1 week
- Row labels represent age years
- Every 10th year label is emphasized
- Four visual states:
  - past
  - current
  - future
  - memo
- Weeks with memos change the cell color itself
- Week selection is inferred from a tap on the year row
- Selected weeks open a bottom modal with details

3.4 Year Mode
- The selected year is shown as 12 vertical month rows
- Each month shows 4 to 5 week blocks in a single row
- Previous / next year navigation is available
- Tapping a block opens the existing week modal

3.5 Weekly Memos
- Text memo per week
- Maximum 200 characters
- Saving closes the modal
- Saving empty text deletes the memo

3.6 Settings
- Birth date
- Life expectancy
- Theme
- Language
- Changes apply immediately without a save button

3.7 Languages
- Japanese
- English
- Chinese
- Spanish
- Hindi

4. Data Persistence
4.1 User Settings
```json
{
  "birthDate": "1990-01-01",
  "language": "ja",
  "lifeExpectancy": 80,
  "selectedCalendarYear": 2026,
  "theme": "light",
  "viewMode": "life"
}
```

4.2 Weekly Memos
```json
{
  "1234": "Went on a trip"
}
```

5. Screen Structure
5.1 Splash
- Title
- Simple icon
- Load saved settings

5.2 Onboarding
- Birth date
- Life expectancy
- Estimated total weeks
- Start button

5.3 Main Screen
- Header: title and settings button
- View switch: `Life / Year`
- Main content: `Life` or `Year`
- Footer: `Left` and progress bar

5.4 Week Detail Modal
- Top handle
- Week title
- Date range
- Previous / next week navigation
- Memo input
- Memo save action

5.5 Settings Screen
- Back button
- Display section
  - Theme
  - Language
- Life section
  - Birth date
  - Life expectancy

6. Design Principles
- Keep borders minimal
- Prioritize grid legibility
- Information priority is `current position -> remaining weeks -> overall view`
- Preserve clear distinction between `past / current / future / memo` in both light and dark modes
- If touch targets become too small, move precision work into a supporting view or UI

7. Future Extensions
- Memo list screen
- Event-week markers
- Month labels in Year mode
- Data export / backup
